The company size and employment type with the most poeple working under it is medium sized companies with full-time working employees at 3139 people for this dataset.¶

Trend from questions 7-9¶

The last 3 questions we asked and got our answers to show an interesting trend. The trend is that each year, the average salary for the specific job of interest is increasing:¶

In [64]:
print('2023 Avg Sal:'+str(sal23))
print('2022 Avg Sal:'+str(sal22))
print('2021 Avg Sal:'+str(sal21))

2023 Avg Sal:171274.57258064515
2022 Avg Sal:153404.30687830687
2021 Avg Sal:118214.28571428571

We can produce a visual representation of this trend via barchart. Put the different working years on the x axis, and the average salaries on the y-axis.¶

In [65]:
x = ['2021','2022','2023']
y = [sal21,sal22,sal23]

data = {'Years': x, 'Salaries': y}

df_chart = pd.DataFrame(data)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))

plt.bar(df_chart['Years'], df_chart['Salaries'])

plt.xlabel('Years',fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Salaries',fontsize=14)
plt.suptitle('Average Salary in USD for Each Working Year.')
plt.xticks(rotation='horizontal')
plt.show()
